{"article_id":"JZdOXc2ptQuz4mzO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"After seven years of promising to repeal the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"Republicans are finally at the point","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"of reckoning","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"- unveiling a replacement plan on Monday","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that upends Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"but will also greatly test President Trump ' s ability","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"to unify Republicans behind it .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"The plan ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"put forward by House Republicans ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"generally follows GOP principles .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"It effectively repeals much-maligned individual and employer insurance mandates ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"which Republicans see as interference in personal health-care choices and markets .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Instead , it provides tax credits","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"for individuals","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to purchase their own policies .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"It also overhauls Medicaid","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"- federally supported health care for the poor -","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"which many Republicans see as too costly","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"as the federal debt approaches $ 20 trillion .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"But independent analysts say","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"the repeal-and-replace plan ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"called the American Health Care Act ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"shows just how difficult it is to have \" insurance for everybody \" and health-care benefits","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that \" beautifully \" cover people ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"as Mr. Trump puts it ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"all while reducing costs .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"\" This is going to be a difficult lift ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and I don ' t see Trump having much sway in this trek","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to repeal","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"and replace , \"","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"says G. William Hoagland , senior vice president of the Bipartisan Policy Center , in an email .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"He estimates","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"that 8 million to 12 million fewer people would be covered under the GOP plan .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"The ACA added coverage for more than 20 million people .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"The independent Congressional Budget Office has yet to report on the plan ' s costs or its effect on the number of insured ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"though other independent analysts","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"contacted by the Monitor","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"agree with Mr. Hoagland","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"that fewer people would be covered .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"\" The House bill is caught in a nasty crossfire \" between conservative and moderate Republicans ,","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"including GOP governors ,","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"writes Lawrence Jacobs , a political science professor and health-care policy expert at the University of Minnesota in Minneapolis , in an email .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"Conservatives view the plan ' s tax credits ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"which would replace Obamacare ' s subsidies ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"as simply a new \" entitlement \" program .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"Moderates , on the other hand , say","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"the tax credits are too meager","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to help low-income Americans ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Professor Jacobs says .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"He adds","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"that many of the 16 Republican governors as well as their Democratic colleagues","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"who expanded Medicaid ' s reach under Obamacare","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"are also sure to object to reduced outlays under the House plan .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Thirty-one states plus the District of Columbia have expanded Medicaid coverage","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"to include more than 11 million people .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"- Effectively drop the individual and employer mandates","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"by repealing their penalties immediately","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"- and retroactively to 2016 .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"It would encourage continuous insurance coverage","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"by having insurers impose a 30 percent boost on premiums","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"if consumers let their coverage lapse .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"- Replace subsidies","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"that help low-income Americans buy private insurance plans on federal insurance market exchanges","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"with tax credits","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"that could be applied to private plans .","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"The credits ,","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"based on age ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"range from a yearly total of $ 2,000 to $ 4,000 for individuals and up to $ 14,000 for families .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"The credits would be applied monthly","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"and are fully refundable ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"which means","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"they would be paid","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"even if a consumer does not owe taxes","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"( this is why conservatives consider this a new entitlement ) .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"The amount of money","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"that patients can save in tax-free Health Savings Accounts","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"would double .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"- Fund expansion under Medicaid fully , but only through 2019 ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"after which the funding would decline .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"In a radical change , all states would get a set amount of money for Medicaid each year","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"based on the size of their state ' s Medicaid population .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"A $ 100 billion \" stability fund \" would be available to all states","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"to use","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"however they want to lower health costs .","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"- Continue the popular parts of Obamacare","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"- allowing young adults to stay on their parents ' health insurance until age 26","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"and prohibiting denial of coverage for a preexisting condition .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"The plan will \" drive down costs ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"encourage competition","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"and give every American access to quality , affordable health insurance , \"","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"said House Speaker Paul Ryan","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"( R )","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"of Wisconsin in a statement Monday night .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"But Democrats strenuously disagree ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"even as premiums have dramatically risen","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"and choices declined in many Obamacare insurance markets .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"So Republicans will have to muscle through the plan on their own ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"using a budget process","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"known as \" reconciliation \"","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"that requires only a majority vote for passage in both houses of Congress .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"Even that low threshold , however , seems elusive","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"given Republican division over the plan .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"\" It still looks like Obamacare-lite to me , \"","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"budget hawk Sen. Rand Paul","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"( R )","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"of Kentucky","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"told reporters Monday evening .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"\" It ' s going to have to be better. \"","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"Two other Senate conservatives have voiced similar objections , as well as House conservatives .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"But on Monday , four GOP senators from states","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that expanded Medicaid","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"went in the other direction .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"They wrote a letter to Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"expressing concern over the House ' s Medicaid reform .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Given their slim majority ,","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"Senate Republicans could afford to lose only two Republicans on repeal-and-replace .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"A Republican health-care expert","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"who helped draft part of the ACA","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"says","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"the concerns over changes to Medicaid are well founded .","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"\" This is a dramatic change to the funding of Medicaid \"","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"that goes \" way beyond \" repealing Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"writes Daniel Derksen , director of the Center for Rural Health at the University of Arizona in Tucson , in an email .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"The capping and then cutting of Medicaid eligibility and funding over several years shifts the costs and risks from the federal government to states , rural hospitals , physicians , and individuals and their families ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"writes Dr. Derksen , a physician .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"That will make it \" much more difficult \" for Medicaid enrollees to remain enrolled","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"and receive the care","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"they need ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"and it will increase the number of charity cases at hospitals ,","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"he says .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":133,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":134,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":135,"text":"Passing health-care reform took more than a century ,","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"as Presidents Harry Truman , Richard Nixon , and Bill Clinton witnessed ,","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"points out Jacobs .","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"It required a filibuster-proof effort of 60 votes in the Senate for President Obama to get there .","depth":4},{"id":139,"text":"\" The House bill starts the process , \"","depth":5},{"id":140,"text":"he writes .","depth":5},{"id":141,"text":"\" The question is whether it has a future . \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":283,"left":271,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":180,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":148,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":147,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":143,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":3,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":4,"right":144,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":144,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":159,"right":178,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":159,"left":150,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":154,"right":157,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":154,"left":151,"right":153,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":12,"right":152,"re